AI Agent Architecture
1. Frontend 

The frontend is where users interact with the AI agent.

Core Features:

Chat or voice interface

Display AI responses (text, images, or voice)

Collect user inputs (queries, commands)

Optional: authentication for personalized experience

Tech Stack:

React.js / Next.js / Angular / Vue.js

Tailwind CSS / Material UI / Bootstrap

State management: Redux / Zustand / Context API

HTTP requests: Axios / Fetch



2. Backend 

The backend handles requests, communicates with the AI model, and manages data.

Core Features:

User Management

Sign up / Login

Role-based access

AI Agent Layer

Receives queries from frontend

Calls AI model (OpenAI GPT, local ML model, or Rasa)

Returns processed responses

Conversation / Interaction Logs

Store chat history for analytics and personalization

Business Logic

Optional domain-specific processing (e.g., e-commerce recommendations, scheduling)

Security

Authentication & authorization

Input sanitization

Tech Stack:

Node.js + Express / Python + FastAPI / Flask

AI/ML API integration:

OpenAI GPT / Azure AI / HuggingFace models

REST API or WebSocket API

JWT / OAuth authentication

3. Database Layer

Database stores users, AI conversation history, and optional analytics.

Essential Collections/Tables:

Users → ID, name, email, role

Conversations / Logs → UserID, timestamp, input, AI response

Preferences → Personalized settings

Analytics / Metrics → Usage patterns, engagement stats

Database Choices:

NoSQL: MongoDB (flexible chat logs)

SQL: PostgreSQL / MySQL (structured user data)

Optional caching: Redis (for session or real-time chat)

4. Optional Services

AI Model Hosting

Cloud (OpenAI, Azure, AWS) or self-hosted ML model

Notification Services

Email or SMS alerts

Analytics / Reporting

Track user engagement or model performance

5. System Flow
[User Browser / App]
          |
          v
   [Frontend UI / Chat Interface]
          |
  WebSocket / HTTP Requests
          |
          v
      [Backend Server]
   -----------------------------
   |             |             |
[Auth]       [AI Agent]   [Database]
               |
           [AI Model / API]
               |
         [Analytics / Logs]


